data.description: 46.86 total acres back along an almost a mile long gravel driveway that is in good shape. Fenced and completely isolated, property straddles Ross and Pike counties and features approximatley 10 acres in pasture and the remainder in  woods.There is a fruit tree orchard with pear, apple and peach trees as well as a grape arbour. The home is 2044 square feet and has 3 large bedrooms and 3 full baths, wrap around porch and oversized attached 2 car garage. There is a pole barn. Public water has been run to the house. New french drains installed as well as new jacks under the house in 2022 from Ohio Basement Authority. Wonderful porch to sit on and take in the spectacular sunsets. Fields have been planted to attract wildlife. Home warranty! Seller will consider paying up to $10,000 in seller concessions/ closing costs. Welcome home!
